 sin\u2014but he did not sin.\n\n  <verse number=\"16\" style=\"v\" />So let us come boldly to Christ, who rules from heaven and does for us what we do not deserve, so that he might kindly help us and have mercy on us when we need him to do so.</para>\n"}], "number": "04", "ref": "", "title": ""}, {"frames": [{"format": "usx", "id": "05-01", "img": "", "text": "<para style=\"p\">\n\n  <verse number=\"1\" style=\"v\" />When God chooses a high priest, he selects a man from the people. This man must serve God for the people; he must give God and sacrifice animals to him for the people's sins. \n\n  <verse number=\"2\" style=\"v\" />A high priest can be gentle with those who know little about God and with those who sin against him. This is because the high priest himself is weak with sin.\n\n  <verse number=\"3\" style=\"v\" />As a result, he also must sacrifice animals, because he sins just like the people do.</para>\n"}, {"format": "usx", "id": "05-04", "img": "", "text": "<verse number=\"4\" style=\"v\" />But no one can honor himself by deciding to become the high priest. Instead, God chose each man to become a high priest, as he chose Aaron to be the first high priest.\n\n<verse number=\"5\" style=\"v\" />Similarly, Christ also did not honor himself by becoming high priest. Instead, God the Father appointed him by saying to him what the Psalmist wrote in the Scriptures:\n\n<para style=\"q1\">\"You are my Son! Today I have declared that I am your Father!\"</para>\n"}, {"format": "usx", "id": "05-06", "img": "", "text": "<para style=\"p\">\n\n  <verse number=\"6\" style=\"v\" />And he also said to Christ what the Psalmist wrote in another Scripture passage:</para>\n\n<para style=\"q1\">\"You are a priest eternally just like Melchizedek was a priest.\"</para>\n"}, {"format": "usx", "id": "05-07", "img": "", "text": "<para style=\"p\">\n\n  <verse number=\"7\" style=\"v\" />When Christ lived on the earth, he prayed  to God and cried out loudly to him in tears. He asked 